text: The Bayer designation γ Normae, which is Latinized as gamma Normae and abbreviated γ Nor, is shared by two stars in the southern constellation of Norma: *γ¹ Normae, an F9 supergiant *γ² Normae, a G8 giant The pair form a double star that can be resolved with the naked eye. ==References== Normae, Gamma Category:Norma (constellation)
title: Gamma Normae
